SUMMARY:Hudson County Teen Arts Festival
DESCRIPTION:Would you like to see some AMAZING art made by local high 
 school artists? Then join us at Bayonne Public Library for the 40th annual 
 Hudson County Alliance of Teen Arts exhibit!  We have art both near the 
 Circulation Desk and upstairs in our Gallery. \n\nThere are literally 
 hundreds of pieces from students in Bayonne\, Jersey City\, Hoboken\, 
 Harrison\, Kearny\, North Bergen\, Secaucus\, Union City\, and Weehawken! 
 \n\nThe exhibit will be available for public viewing from today (Tuesday\, 
 May 12th) through Saturday\, May 23rd. And on Wednesday\, May 20th at 7 
 pm\, there will be an Awards Ceremony! @sunspirecafe will be at the awards 
 ceremony too\, keeping you caffeinated for your evening!\n\nFrom sculpture 
 to digital art to canvas and print making\, we’ve got it all. We hope to 
 see you here supporting our local student artists!
LOCATION:Downstairs Display Cases\, Gallery\, Lobby\, Upstairs Display Cases
ORGANIZER;CN="Melody Scagnelli-Townley":MAILTO:mtownley@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adults, Art Show, Children's Events, STEM/STEAM, Teen Events, Tween Events
UID:LibCal-17197-15447688
URL:https://bayonnelibrary.libcal.com/event/15447688
END:VEVENT
