DTSTART:20260512T230000Z
DTEND:20260513T004500Z
DTSTAMP:20260512T000000Z
SUMMARY:Bayonne Historical Society Program: "Just What the Heck is an Archives Room Anyway?"
DESCRIPTION:Join the Bayonne Historical Society at the Bayonne Public 
 Library for a special lecture held on Tuesday\, May 12th at 7 pm in the 
 Gallery: “Just What the Heck is an Archives Room Anyway?” \n\nThere is 
 a wealth of information about the history of the City of Bayonne in the 
 Bayonne Public Library.  Much of it resides in the Library’s Archives 
 Room.  But just what is an Archives Room?  Librarian Bill Fischer will 
 discuss the resources of the Bayonne Public Library and how they can be 
 used to investigate the history of Bayonne. He will share some interesting 
 items from the collection and also discuss digital resources.  A question 
 and answer period will follow. \n\nNo advanced registration is required. 
 Light refreshments provided. We hope to see you there!
LOCATION:Small Programming Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Melody Scagnelli-Townley":MAILTO:mtownley@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adults, Historical Society, Meeting, Teen Events
UID:LibCal-17197-16329689
URL:https://bayonnelibrary.libcal.com/event/16329689
END:VEVENT
