SUMMARY:Read to a Dog
DESCRIPTION:\n\nJoin us at the Bayonne Public Library on Monday\, May 18th 
 at 6 pm in the Small Programming Room for a Read to a Dog event! \n\nMeet 
 Lucy the Golden Retriever! Each child will have a few minutes to read to 
 Lucy and practice their reading skills. Please either bring the book you 
 would like to read or arrive a few minutes early so that you have time to 
 choose one at the library.\n\nAdvanced registration is required. Walk-ins 
 will be included if space permits.\n\n** Please make sure you are 
 comfortable being around dogs and have no allergies before 
 registering**\n\nLucy has been a therapy dog since 2023. She is an AKC 
 golden retriever. She has earned all her AKC canine good citizen titles: 
 CGC\, CGCA\, CGCU and the AKC therapy dog title.She has also earned her AKC 
 novice trick dog title.\n\n
LOCATION:Small Programming Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Jake Russell":MAILTO:jrussell@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Children's Events, Storytime, Tween Events
UID:LibCal-17197-16540960
URL:https://bayonnelibrary.libcal.com/event/16540960
END:VEVENT
