SUMMARY:Tech Thursdays: Ask Me Anything
DESCRIPTION:Want to learn how to use the computer\, but never knew who to 
 ask? Need assistance navigating the internet? Want to learn how to set up 
 and use an email account? Have a burning tech question\, but we haven’t 
 covered the issue in one of our tech classes yet?\n\n \n\nBayonne Public 
 Library can help!  Every Thursday in May from 2:30-3:30 PM in the Small 
 Programming Room\, we will be offering a Tech Thursday class with our Adult 
 Services Librarian\, Bill Fischer.  The following classes will be offered 
 in May:\n\n \n\n\n	May 7th - Computer Basics\n	May 14th - Internet 
 Basics\n	May 21st - Email Basics\n	May 28th - Ask Me Anything\n\n\n 
 \n\nFeel free to attend one - or all!  - of our Tech Thursdays classes!  
 During our Ask Me Anything class\, you can ask any miscellaneous tech 
 related questions that you might have!  Advanced registration is 
 preferred\, but walk-ins will be accommodated if possible.  \n\n 
 \n\nRegister for the classes by clicking the link in our Bio or by going to 
 our calendar (https://bayonnelibrary.libcal.com)\, clicking on the 
 class(es) that are of interest to you\, and clicking “Begin 
 Registration” OR call our Reference Desk at (201) 858-6970 ext.1 and the 
 Librarian on desk can help you register.  \n\n \n\n#Bayonne #BayonneNJ 
 #TechThursdays #ComputerClass #AMA #AMA #EmailBasics #InternetBasics 
 #ComputerBasics
LOCATION:Small Programming Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Narissa Palmer":MAILTO:npalmer@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adults, Seniors, Tech Classes
