SUMMARY:Free Childhood Vaccination Clinic (Ages 18 and Under)
DESCRIPTION:Join us at the Bayonne Public Library for free vaccination 
 clinics for children! \n\nThere will be clinics from 2 to 5 pm in the 2nd 
 Floor Gallery on the following dates: \n\n\n	Wednesday\, January 
 14th\n	Tuesday\, February 3rd\n	Wednesday\, March 11th\n	Tuesday\, April 
 7th\n	Tuesday\, May 5th\n	Tuesday\, June 2nd\n\n\nThis program is brought 
 to you by the Hudson Regional Health Commission (HRHC) and the Bayonne 
 Health Department. \n\nAll the recommended childhood vaccinations required 
 for school are available free of charge for children ages 18 and under 
 without health insurance. Available vaccinations include: COVID-19\, DTaP\, 
 Hepatitis A&B\, HPV\, Flu\, Polio\, MMR\, Rotavirus\, Varicella\, RSV\, and 
 more. \n\nWhat are the requirements for participating?\n\n\n	You must have 
 no insurance OR be eligible for Medicaid OR be part of NJ FamilyCare Plan 
 A\n	You must be 18 years old and under\n\n\n***Please note that anyone who 
 is 18 & under and identifies as American Indian or Alaskan Native is 
 eligible for the vaccinations regardless of their insurance 
 status.***\n\nWhat do you need to do to participate?\n\nAdvanced 
 registration is required. Register by going to 
 https://hudsonregional.gov/vfc You will be contacted by an HRHC 
 representative to confirm your eligibility and schedule your appointment! 
 Registration closes one week prior to the clinic.\n\nTo learn more\, email 
 hcvax@hudsonregional.gov \n\n
LOCATION:Gallery
ORGANIZER;CN="Melody Scagnelli-Townley":MAILTO:mtownley@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Children's Events, Teen Events, Tween Events, Vaccination Clinic
