SUMMARY:Community of Lifesavers: Hands-On CPR & AED Training
DESCRIPTION:Join Hackensack Meridian Health at the Bayonne Public Library 
 on Tuesday\, June 9th at 7 pm in the Gallery for a free\, hands-on CPR and 
 AED training presented in both English and Spanish! \n\nIn this 
 non-certification class from the American Heart Association\, you will 
 learn how early intervention can save a life. Emphasis will be placed on 
 the importance of hands-only CPR\, and you will have the opportunity to 
 practice effective chest compressions on a manikin and learn how to operate 
 an automated external defibrillator (AED).\n\nThis class is open to anyone 
 ages 14 and older who wants to gain the skills and confidence to act in an 
 emergency. Advanced registration is required. Become a lifesaver in your 
 community!
LOCATION:Small Programming Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Melody Scagnelli-Townley":MAILTO:mtownley@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adults, Presentation, Seniors, Social Work, Teen Events, Tween Events
