SUMMARY:"Read and Watch" Book Club
DESCRIPTION:Join us at the Bayonne Public Library for a Read & Watch book 
 club for young adults! \n\nThis two-part event will meet first on 
 Thursday\, June 11th from 6:30-8:30 pm to discuss the first volume of 
 "Heartstopper\," a graphic novel by Alice Oseman. If you have not already 
 read the book\, make sure to check it out ahead of time and bring your 
 thoughts to share with other tweens and teens. \n\nWe will meet again on 
 Thursday\, June 25th from 6:30-8:30 pm and we will watch the first two 
 episodes of the Heartstopper series on Netflix. \n\nThis program is for 
 tweens and teens ages 12-18 and will take place in the Art & Music Room on 
 the 2nd floor of the library. Snacks will be provided. \n\nAdvanced 
 registration is recommended\, but not required. Walk-ins will be 
 accommodated if space permits. \n\nWhat's the book about? Shy and 
 softhearted Charlie Spring sits next to rugby player Nick Nelson in class 
 one morning. A warm and intimate friendship follows\, and that soon 
 develops into something more for Charlie\, who doesn't think he has a 
 chance. But Nick is struggling with feelings of his own\, and as the two 
 grow closer and take on the ups and downs of high school\, they come to 
 understand the surprising and delightful ways in which love works.\n\n\nHow 
 can you participate? Bayonne Public Library has eBook and eAudiobook copies 
 available via hoopla as well as physical book copies. If you’d prefer to 
 purchase your own physical copy\, we recommend purchasing from The Little 
 Boho Bookshop\, our favorite local bookshop\, located at 164A Broadway or 
 online at https://thelittlebohobookshop.com/.\n
LOCATION:Art & Music
ORGANIZER;CN="Melody Scagnelli-Townley":MAILTO:mtownley@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Book Club, Teen Events, Tween Events
UID:LibCal-17197-16721582
URL:https://bayonnelibrary.libcal.com/calendar/BPL/June2026RandWPt2
END:VEVENT
