SUMMARY:Bayonne Feral Cat Foundation Adoption Event
DESCRIPTION:Join us on Saturday\, June 13th at the Bayonne Public Library 
 in the Gallery from 10 am to 3 pm for a very special “Cats\, Coffee\, & 
 Books Adoption Event”! \n\nStop by to meet some wonderful cats hoping to 
 find their forever families. We will have kittens\, adults\, and senior 
 cats. Whether you’re looking for a playful baby\, a calm companion\, or 
 your new best friend\, there’s a cat waiting for you!\n\nSunspire Cafe 
 will be popping up in the Lobby offering some fun cat-themed drinks for 
 sale.\n\nYour support - whether through adoption\, donation\, or simply 
 spreading the word - helps Bayonne Feral Cat Foundation and Furvana Cat 
 Rescue continue their mission of giving these deserving cats a second 
 chance at life. Spend some time getting to know the cats’ unique 
 personalities\, learn about the heart of rescue work\, and discover how you 
 can make a lasting difference. Together\, we can create a brighter future - 
 one life\, one love\, one home at a time!\n\n \n\nUPDATE THIS
LOCATION:Gallery\, Lobby
ORGANIZER;CN="Melody Scagnelli-Townley":MAILTO:mtownley@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adults, Children's Events, Meeting, Seniors, Teen Events, Tween Events
UID:LibCal-17197-16805279
URL:https://bayonnelibrary.libcal.com/event/16805279
END:VEVENT
