SUMMARY:Exploration Station
DESCRIPTION:Join us at the Bayonne Public Library for a monthly 
 “Exploration Station” program in the Small Programming Room on the 
 following Thursdays:\n\n\n	February 26th\n	March 19th\n	April 23rd\n	May 
 28th\n	June 25th\n	July 23rd\n	August 20th\n	September 24th\n	October 
 15th\n	November 19th\n	December 17th\n\n\nDiscover the magic of learning 
 through hands-on\, sensory play programs that are designed to engage 
 toddlers and preschoolers in imaginative and educational activities. Each 
 session is a journey through themed stations that stimulate children’s 
 senses and curiosity while promoting early literacy\, cognitive 
 development\, and improving social skills. \n\nThis program is for ages 5 
 and under. On each day\, the program will run twice: once from 10-10:50 am 
 and once from 11-11:50 am. Both sessions are the same. Advanced 
 registration is required. Please register for only ONE of the two sessions. 
 Please only register the children attending\; do not register the adults 
 attending. Walk-ins will be accommodated if space permits. We hope to see 
 you there!
LOCATION:Small Programming Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Jake Russell":MAILTO:jrussell@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Children's Events, STEM/STEAM
UID:LibCal-17197-16425955
URL:https://bayonnelibrary.libcal.com/event/16425955
END:VEVENT
