SUMMARY:Flu and COVID Vaccination Clinic
DESCRIPTION:Join us at the Bayonne Public Library for free seasonal flu and 
 COVID vaccination clinics!\n\nThere will be clinics from 10:30 am to 5 pm 
 in the 2nd Floor Gallery on the following Thursdays: \n\n\n	January 
 29th\n	February 26th\n	March 26th\n	April 23rd \n	May 28th\n	June 
 25th\n\n\nFlu and/or COVID vaccinations are available free of charge 
 regardless of insurance status. \n\n***Please note that COVID shots are 
 only available for ages 65 older or those with pre-existing conditions and 
 flu shots are only available for ages 18 & older. Those under 18 can 
 receive flu and COVID shots at our monthly “Vaccines for Children” 
 clinic.***\n\nThis program is brought to you by the Hudson Regional Health 
 Commission (HRHC) and the Bayonne Health Department. \n\nTo learn more\, 
 email hcvax@hudsonregional.gov
LOCATION:Gallery
ORGANIZER;CN="Melody Scagnelli-Townley":MAILTO:mtownley@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adults, Children's Events, Seniors, Social Work, Teen Events, Tween Events, Vaccination Clinic
