SUMMARY:Tech Thursdays: Ask Me Anything
DESCRIPTION:Want to learn how to use the computer\, but never knew who to 
 ask? Want to learn about online shopping? Do you want to stay safe online? 
 Worried about viruses\, phishing\, and ransomware? Have a burning tech 
 question\, but we haven’t covered the issue in one of our tech classes 
 yet?  \n\n \n\nBayonne Public Library can help! Most Thursdays in June from 
 2:30-3:30 PM in the Small Programming Room\, we will be offering a Tech 
 Thursday class with our Adult Services Librarian\, Bill Fischer. The 
 following classes will be offered in June:\n\n \n\n\n	June 4 - Online 
 Shopping\n	June 11 - Computer Safety & Security \n	June 18 - No 
 Class\n	June 25 - Ask Me Anything\n\n\n \n\nFeel free to attend one - or 
 all!  - of our Tech Thursdays classes! During our Ask Me Anything class\, 
 you can ask any miscellaneous tech related questions that you might have! 
 Advanced registration is preferred\, but walk-ins will be accommodated if 
 possible.  \n\n \n\nRegister for the classes by clicking the link in our 
 Bio or by going to our calendar (https://bayonnelibrary.libcal.com)\, 
 clicking on the class(es) that are of interest to you\, and clicking 
 “Begin Registration” OR call our Reference Desk at (201) 858-6970 ext.1 
 and the Librarian on desk can help you register.  \n\n \n\n#Bayonne 
 #BayonneNJ #TechThursdays #ComputerClass #OnlineShopping #OnlineSafety #AMA 
 \n\n\n \n\n
LOCATION:Small Programming Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Narissa Palmer":MAILTO:npalmer@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adults, Seniors, Tech Classes
UID:LibCal-17197-16967989
URL:https://bayonnelibrary.libcal.com/event/16967989
