SUMMARY:Poker Strategy & Decision-Making for Teens
DESCRIPTION:Join us at the Bayonne Public Library on Monday\, June 29th at 
 6:30 pm in the Small Programming Room for a special poker class for teens. 
 \n\nIn this class\, attendees will learn how the insights\, strategies\, 
 and probability skills used in playing poker can help with increasing 
 confidence and decision making in other areas of life. This class includes 
 a presentation\, guided gameplay\, and a Q&A reflection time. \n\nThe 
 recommended age range for attendance is 13-18 years old. Advanced 
 registration is required. Walk-ins will be accommodated if space permits.
