DTSTAMP:20260709T000000Z
SUMMARY:America 250 Piano Performance
DESCRIPTION:Join us at the Bayonne Public Library on Thursday\, July 9th at 
 7 pm in the Gallery for a very special American 250 piano concert!\n\nThis 
 Americana-themed piano performance will be played by Laith Khan. Laith is a 
 12-year-old Bayonne native who lives and attends school at Midtown. He has 
 been part of the Gifted and Talented Program for music for several years. A 
 self-taught musician\, Laith plays entirely by ear and can hear a piece for 
 the first time and play it without ever having had formal lessons or 
 training. He first began playing music at just two years old\, surprising 
 his family by spontaneously playing Bach on toy instruments. \n\nLaith 
 plays a variety of instruments\, including piano\, violin\, cello\, 
 guitar\, clarinet\, accordion\, glockenspiel\, drums\, and more. He has 
 performed at school concerts and throughout the Bayonne community\, 
 including opening Bayonne Board of Education meetings with the National 
 Anthem for years\, performing for Bayonne Recreation’s Special Needs 
 Sports Photo Exhibit\, and playing for Buddy Baseball’s opening day\, 
 where he is also a proud athlete.\n\nLaith has a deep love for music and 
 for his Bayonne community. He enjoys connecting with others through his 
 performances and sharing the joy that music brings to him and others.\n\nWe 
 hope you’ll join us for a patriotic concert! The concert is free\, open 
 to all ages\, and no advanced registration is required.\n\n
LOCATION:Gallery
ORGANIZER;CN="Melody Scagnelli-Townley":MAILTO:mtownley@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adults, Children's Events, Concerts, Holidays, Seniors, Tech Classes, Tween Events
UID:LibCal-17197-16778482
URL:https://bayonnelibrary.libcal.com/event/16778482
END:VEVENT
