BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260723T213000Z
DTEND:20260724T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260723T000000Z
SUMMARY:Book a Librarian
DESCRIPTION:Do you need help with an online application?  Do you want to 
 set up an email account but don’t know how?  Do you need assistance with 
 tracing  your family tree? \n\nThe Bayonne Public Library is pleased to 
 announce a new service: Book A Librarian! Currently\, all appointments are 
 on Thursday evenings between 5:30 and 7:30 pm. \n\nBayonne patrons may 
 schedule an appointment for individualized assistance on a variety of 
 topics. \n\n \n\nWe can help with:\n\n\n	Online applications\n	Research 
 including local history & genealogy\n	Using Library resources such as 
 databases\, ebooks\, streaming TV & movies\, and Mango Languages\n	Setting 
 up an email account\n	Scanning & emailing a document\n	And many other 
 topics! \n\n\nPatrons with a valid Bayonne Public Library card may book one 
 45 minute appointment per month.\n\nPlease email refdesk@bayonnelibrary.org 
 or call 201-858-6980 to schedule an appointment.  Please include your 
 name\, email\, telephone\, library card number\, and the topic with which 
 you would like to receive assistance.
LOCATION:Small Programming Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Bill Fischer":MAILTO:wfischer@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adults, Meeting, Seniors, Social Work, Tech Classes
UID:LibCal-17197-15951301
URL:https://bayonnelibrary.libcal.com/event/15951301
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260723T223000Z
DTEND:20260724T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260723T000000Z
SUMMARY:English As A Second Language (ESL) Conversation Group
DESCRIPTION:Join us at the Bayonne Public Library for a weekly English as a 
 Second Language (ESL) Conversation Group! This group will meet twice per 
 week in Classroom B: one morning session and one evening session.\n\nThe 
 Monday morning group is from 10-11:30 am and will meet on the following 
 dates:\n\n\n	May 4 and 18\n	June 8 & 22\n	July 6 & 20\n	August 10 & 
 24\n\n\nThe Thursday evening group is from 6:30-8 pm and will meet on the 
 following dates:\n\n\n	May 7 & 21\n	June 11 & 25\n	July 9 & 23\n	August 13 
 & 27\n\n\nThis group is intended for people with basic English skills. No 
 advanced registration is required. Attendees are welcome to attend both 
 sessions each week\, if desired.
LOCATION:Classroom B
ORGANIZER;CN="Melody Scagnelli-Townley":MAILTO:mtownley@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adults, ESL, Seniors, Teen Events
UID:LibCal-17197-16618570
URL:https://bayonnelibrary.libcal.com/event/16618570
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260723T230000Z
DTEND:20260724T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260723T000000Z
SUMMARY:Mortgage Support Tabling: The Waterfront Project
DESCRIPTION:Join the Bayonne Public Library and The Waterfront Project on 
 Thursday\, July 16th and Thursday\, July 23rd from 7-8 pm in the Lobby for 
 free mortgage support resources and assistance. \n\nRepresentatives from 
 The Waterfront Project will be available to provide reliable information\, 
 help you explore your options\, and connect you with resources that can 
 help you stay housed. \n\nNo advanced registration is needed. Just walk in 
 and you can receive assistance.\n
LOCATION:Lobby
ORGANIZER;CN="Melody Scagnelli-Townley":MAILTO:mtownley@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adults, Seniors, Social Work, Tabling
UID:LibCal-17197-16747104
URL:https://bayonnelibrary.libcal.com/event/16747104
END:VEVENT
