SUMMARY:Tween Dungeons & Dragons
DESCRIPTION:Watched Stranger Things and want to try some Dungeons & 
 Dragons? Looking for a good after school activity? Used to play but can’t 
 find enough friends for a campaign? Want to make some fun new 
 friends?\n\nThen join us at the Bayonne Public Library for Dungeons & 
 Dragons! What’s that? Dungeons & Dragons (D&D) is a fantasy tabletop 
 role-playing game where the players form an adventuring party who explore 
 fantasy worlds together as they embark on epic quests and level up in 
 experience. \n\nThis every-other-Tuesday gaming session is run by a 
 professional Dungeon Master on the following dates:\n\n\n	\n	January 13 and 
 27\n	February 10 & 24\n	March 10 & 24\n	April 7 & 21\n	May 5 & 19\n	June 
 2\, 16\, & 30\n	July 14 & 28\n	August 11 & 25\n	September 8 & 22\n	October 
 6 & 20\n	November 3 & 17\n	December 1 & 15\n	\n\n\nAges 9 to 12 meet from 
 4-6 pm and Ages 13  meet from 6:30-8:30 pm in the Small Programming Room of 
 the Bayonne Public Library.\n\nAdvanced registration is required for every 
 session individually. Walk-ins will be included if space permits.\n\n\n\n\n
LOCATION:Small Programming Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Melody Scagnelli-Townley":MAILTO:mtownley@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Children's Events, Tween Events
UID:LibCal-17197-16203001
URL:https://bayonnelibrary.libcal.com/event/16203001
END:VEVENT
