SUMMARY:Yarn Group & Knitting Class
DESCRIPTION:Join Susan Averello at the Bayonne Public Library for a yarn 
 group & knitting class! She has been knitting for over 30 years and she can 
 also crochet. She has worked at Michaels as a knitting teacher and with 
 Crafty Fox Studios until the studio closed. \n\nThe group will meet on 
 Tuesdays from 7-8:30 pm in the Art & Music Room on the 2nd floor of the 
 Bayonne Public Library.\n\nKnitters and crocheters of all experience levels 
 are welcome\, including those who would like to learn. No registration is 
 required. \n\nIf you are an experienced knitter or crocheter\, please bring 
 with you whatever project you're currently working on. If you are an 
 inexperienced knitter or crocheter who would like to learn\, please bring 
 size 7 knitting needles and a light colored\, worsted weight yarn. \n\nFor 
 more information\, check the Facebook group\, “Bayonne Knitters and 
 Crafters”.\n\n
LOCATION:Art & Music
ORGANIZER;CN="Melody Scagnelli-Townley":MAILTO:mtownley@bayonnelibrary.org
