SUMMARY:Multiple Sclerosis Monthly Support Meeting
DESCRIPTION:Join the Bayonne Public Library and the Multiple Sclerosis 
 Foundation for a monthly Multiple Sclerosis (MS) meeting. This meeting is a 
 welcoming and supportive space for individuals living with MS\, their 
 families\, and caregivers. \n\nEach session provides an opportunity to 
 share experiences\, learn practical tips for managing symptoms\, and hear 
 from guest speakers on topics related to health\, wellness\, & living well 
 with MS. The group fosters connection\, encouragement\, and a sense of 
 community\, reminding members that they are not alone on their 
 journey.\n\nThe group will meet on the following Wednesdays from 5-7 pm in 
 Classrooms C&D\n\n\n	January 21st\n	February 18th\n	March 18th\n	April 
 22nd\n	May 20th\n	June 24th\n	July 22nd\n	August 19th\n	September 
 23rd\n	October 21st\n	November 18th\n	December 16th\n\n\nNo advanced 
 registration is required. We hope to see you there!\n\n
LOCATION:Classrooms C&D
ORGANIZER;CN="Narissa Palmer":MAILTO:npalmer@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adults, Meeting, Seniors, Teen Events
UID:LibCal-17197-16001088
URL:https://bayonnelibrary.libcal.com/event/16001088
END:VEVENT
