DTEND:20261030T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20261029T000000Z
SUMMARY:Book a Librarian
DESCRIPTION:Do you need help with an online application?  Do you want to 
 set up an email account but don’t know how?  Do you need assistance with 
 tracing  your family tree? \n\nThe Bayonne Public Library is pleased to 
 announce a new service: Book A Librarian! Currently\, all appointments are 
 on Thursday evenings between 5:30 and 7:30 pm. \n\nBayonne patrons may 
 schedule an appointment for individualized assistance on a variety of 
 topics. \n\n \n\nWe can help with:\n\n\n	Online applications\n	Research 
 including local history & genealogy\n	Using Library resources such as 
 databases\, ebooks\, streaming TV & movies\, and Mango Languages\n	Setting 
 up an email account\n	Scanning & emailing a document\n	And many other 
 topics! \n\n\nPatrons with a valid Bayonne Public Library card may book one 
 45 minute appointment per month.\n\nPlease email refdesk@bayonnelibrary.org 
 or call 201-858-6980 to schedule an appointment.  Please include your 
 name\, email\, telephone\, library card number\, and the topic with which 
 you would like to receive assistance.
LOCATION:Classrooms C&D
ORGANIZER;CN="Bill Fischer":MAILTO:wfischer@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adults, Meeting, Seniors, Social Work, Tech Classes
UID:LibCal-17197-15951315
URL:https://bayonnelibrary.libcal.com/event/15951315
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20261030T143000Z
DTEND:20261030T151500Z
DTSTAMP:20261030T000000Z
SUMMARY:Caregiver and Me Pilates Class
DESCRIPTION:Join the Bayonne Public Library for a “Caregiver and Me” 
 Pilates class! The class will meet twice monthly from 10:30-11:30 am in 
 Gallery on the following Fridays:\n\n\n	March 13\n	April 24\n	May 29\n	June 
 26\n	July 17 & 31\n	August 14 & 28\n	September 4 & 18\n	October 16 & 
 30\n	November 13\n	December 11 \n\n\nWhat is “Caregiver and Me” Pilates 
 class? It’s a blend of gentle exercise and playful\, child-friendly 
 activities. It’s specially designed for caregivers to strengthen their 
 bodies while introducing little ones to the joy of movement. With gentle 
 Pilates exercises modified for both adults and kids\, these classes create 
 a space for connection\, fitness\, and fun.\n\nAdvanced registration is 
 required. Please be sure to register individually for all classes you would 
 like to attend. Walk-ins will be included if space permits.
LOCATION:Gallery
ORGANIZER;CN="Narissa Palmer":MAILTO:npalmer@bayonnelibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adults, Children's Events, Fitness Class
UID:LibCal-17197-16389689
URL:https://bayonnelibrary.libcal.com/event/16389689
END:VEVENT
